40:56.387 --> 41:01.526 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The "Independent Lens"
documentary "The Black
Panthers: Vanguard of the
Revolution," airs

41:01.626 --> 41:08.166 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
tonight on PBS stations. It
traces the group's
origins and influence on U.S.
politics and

41:08.266 --> 41:10.301 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
culture in the 1960s

41:10.401 --> 41:13.304 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MAN: Black Panthers were
absolutely unique.

41:13.404 --> 41:18.843 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN: Police jump on you, beat
you up. This
is what we were going through on
a daily basis.

41:18.943 --> 41:21.479 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN: Now we had voices that were
not going
to turn the other cheek.

41:21.579 --> 41:25.917 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
MAN: Stop brutalizing our
community, or we're
going to drive you pigs out.

41:26.017 --> 41:29.554 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN: We don't hate those guys
because of their
color. We hate oppression.

41:29.654 --> 41:32.156 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MAN: We wanted the entire
community to follow.

41:32.256 --> 41:36.027 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Jeffrey Brown is
back with his
conversation with the film's
award-winning

41:36.127 --> 41:37.862 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
director, Stanley Nelson.

41:37.962 --> 41:39.731 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Stanley Nelson,
welcome to
you.

41:39.831 --> 41:41.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STANLEY NELSON, Director, "The
Black Panthers:
Vanguard of the Revolution":
Thank you.

41:41.866 --> 41:47.538 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Did this begin
for you from
a sense that the Black Panthers
were misunderstood,

41:47.638 --> 41:50.375 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
not well-remembered, forgotten
altogether?
What's the beginning?

41:50.475 --> 41:52.910 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
STANLEY NELSON: I think it was
that they were
misunderstood.

41:53.010 --> 41:57.982 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think that the Panthers are
well-remembered,
but I think that people don't
understand who

41:58.082 --> 42:04.422 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the Panthers were and don't
understand how
the Panthers were thought of
back then in

42:04.522 --> 42:07.592 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the '60s. So, I thought that it
was really
ripe for a new telling.

42:07.692 --> 42:12.663 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Well, given the
controversy
back then to this day, right,
and it's such

42:12.764 --> 42:16.467 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a lot of -- there's a lot of
history to get
your arms around. How did you --
how much

42:16.567 --> 42:18.336 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
did you think you could tell?

42:18.436 --> 42:22.473 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STANLEY NELSON: You know, I
think it started
out as a three-hour project, and
we realized

42:22.573 --> 42:24.942 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that two hours was about the
limit.

42:25.042 --> 42:30.014 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, you know, we knew that we
couldn't tell
every single thing, and we knew
that we had

42:30.114 --> 42:35.219 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to stop and start somewhere, so
the film really
begins with the beginning of the
Panthers

42:35.319 --> 42:39.957 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in 1966 and goes kind of through
their height,
their heyday, and ends in 1973.

42:40.057 --> 42:46.264 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And misunderstood
in the sense
that -- which part did you feel
you most needed

42:46.364 --> 42:48.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to -- I don't know if correct is
the right
word.

42:49.000 --> 42:53.638 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STANLEY NELSON: I think the
Panthers are really
interesting because they're both
demonized

42:53.738 --> 42:56.941 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and they're mythologized at the
same time.

42:57.041 --> 43:03.147 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think that both groups get
it wrong.
And I think that, a lot of
times, it's oversimplified,

43:03.247 --> 43:08.286 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
they were bad or they were
great. And there's
a lot of nuance to the Panthers'
story, and

43:08.386 --> 43:10.188 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
we wanted to really get that out
in this film.

43:10.288 --> 43:13.691 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And so you're
showing -- you're
certainly showing the social
programs that

43:13.791 --> 43:17.795 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
they were involved in, but at
the same time,
of course, it begins with guns,
with young

43:17.895 --> 43:20.231 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
black men and women in the
streets of Oakland.

43:20.331 --> 43:25.603 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STANLEY NELSON: Well, it began
as a way of,
as the Panthers would have put
it, to kind

43:25.703 --> 43:28.840 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of defend the community against
the brutality
of the police.

43:28.940 --> 43:34.679 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At that point, the Oakland
Police Department
was notoriously brutal. And the
Panthers,

43:34.779 --> 43:38.649 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
there was a quirk in the law, an
open-carry
law in California that kind of
nobody knew

43:38.749 --> 43:42.820 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
about it, but it said that you
could carry
a loaded weapon as long as you
carried it

43:42.920 --> 43:44.722 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
out in the open.

43:44.822 --> 43:48.092 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, the Panthers said, OK, well,
we will police
the police. We will follow the
police and,

43:48.192 --> 43:52.530 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
as they put it, make sure that
no brutality
occurs when the police stop
somebody.

43:52.630 --> 43:56.300 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right, I have
a -- we have
a short clip I want to show.
This is a little

43:56.400 --> 44:00.438 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
-- catching a little bit of the
spirit of
the times. Right? OK. Let's take
a look at

44:00.538 --> 44:01.506 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
that.

44:01.606 --> 44:04.809 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
STANLEY NELSON: OK.

44:04.909 --> 44:21.192 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WOMAN: This brother here,
myself, all of us
were born with our hair like
this, and we

44:21.292 --> 44:23.494 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
just wear it like this. The
reason for it,
you might say, is like a new
awareness among

44:23.594 --> 44:29.867 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
black people that their own
natural appearance,
physical appearance, is
beautiful. Black people

44:29.967 --> 44:42.246 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are aware now. They're proud of
it. It's pleasing
to them. Isn't it beautiful? All
right.

44:42.346 --> 44:44.549 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

44:44.649 --> 44:58.329 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN: You're talking about
people who were
teenagers 17, 18, 19, 20. That's
the bulk

44:58.429 --> 45:03.434 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of the Panthers are teenagers.
So the fact
that we were so young and the
fact that this

45:03.534 --> 45:09.640 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
hadn't happened before, I'm not
certain that
we recognized how startling it
looked to other

45:09.740 --> 45:10.641 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
people.

45:10.741 --> 45:12.476 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: How startling it
looked.

45:12.577 --> 45:17.782 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, you cannot tell the
story of the Black
Panthers without reminding us of
the feel

45:17.882 --> 45:20.918 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the time, right, through the
music, through
the pictures and all.

45:21.018 --> 45:23.955 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STANLEY NELSON: Yes, I think
that that was
really important to us making
the film, is

45:24.055 --> 45:29.794 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that you had to understand the
times a little
bit. We had to get you back
there to understand

45:29.894 --> 45:33.197 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the Panthers at all, or else it
doesn't make
any sense.

45:33.297 --> 45:37.335 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think that one of the
things that we
were able to use was music, you
know, the

45:37.435 --> 45:43.608 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
music of the times, the music
where the songs
are, "Am I Black Enough For You"
or "All Power

45:43.708 --> 45:48.546 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to the People." You know, those
-- that was
the music and that kind of sets
a base, I

45:48.646 --> 45:51.916 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
think, for what comes later in
the film.

